---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — gpulse"
  description="Terms of Service for the gpulse GPU monitoring tool and gpulse.ai website."
>
  <section class="px-4 pt-32 pb-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">

      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="text-sm text-muted transition-colors hover:text-cyan">
          &larr; Back to Home
        </a>
      </nav>

      <!-- Page header -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-muted text-lg">
          Effective Date: <time datetime="2026-03-21">March 21, 2026</time>
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="space-y-12 text-muted leading-relaxed">

        <!-- 1. Agreement -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">1. Agreement</h2>
          <p>
            By downloading, installing, or using gpulse ("Software") or visiting gpulse.ai ("Website"), you agree to these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree, do not use the Software or Website.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            These Terms are between you and Karthik Kirubakaran ("Author," "we," "us"), the developer and owner of gpulse.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. License -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">2. License</h2>
          <p>
            We grant you a <strong class="text-white">limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable</strong> license to use the compiled gpulse binary for GPU monitoring on devices you own or control. This license covers personal and commercial use.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            This license does not include access to source code. The Software is distributed as a compiled binary only.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. Restrictions -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">3. Restrictions</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software;</li>
            <li>Modify, adapt, or create derivative works from the Software;</li>
            <li>Redistribute, sublicense, rent, sell, or transfer the Software to third parties;</li>
            <li>Remove or alter any proprietary notices on the Software;</li>
            <li>Use the Software to build a competing product.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. Ownership -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">4. Ownership</h2>
          <p>
            The Software, including all code, design, and documentation, is the exclusive property of Karthik Kirubakaran. All rights not expressly granted here are reserved.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            "gpulse" and associated branding are trademarks of Karthik Kirubakaran. You may reference gpulse by name for identification purposes consistent with fair use.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            If you provide feedback or suggestions about the Software, you grant us a perpetual, royalty-free license to use that feedback without obligation to you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 5. Free Tier -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">5. Free Tier</h2>
          <p>
            The free tier provides local GPU monitoring with no time limit. It includes real-time metrics, memory tracking, process monitoring, and the terminal interface.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We may adjust which features are included in the free tier. If we materially reduce free tier functionality, we will provide 30 days' notice on the Website.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 6. Paid Plans -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">6. Paid Plans</h2>
          <p>
            When available, Pro ($29/month) and Enterprise subscriptions will be governed by these additional terms:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>Subscriptions are billed on a recurring basis through a third-party payment processor.</li>
            <li>You may cancel at any time. Access continues through the end of your current billing period.</li>
            <li>We may change pricing with 30 days' written notice. Continued use after a price change constitutes acceptance.</li>
            <li>No refunds for partial billing periods.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- 7. Privacy -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">7. Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            The gpulse CLI collects <strong class="text-white">zero user data</strong>. No telemetry, no analytics, no network calls. All GPU data stays on your machine.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The only optional network feature is the Prometheus metrics endpoint, which you must explicitly configure. For Website data practices, see our <a href="/privacy" class="text-cyan hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 8. Third-Party Components -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">8. Third-Party Components</h2>
          <p>
            The Software includes open-source libraries governed by their own licenses. License notices for all third-party components are bundled with the binary. We make no additional warranties for third-party components beyond those in their respective licenses.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 9. No Warranty -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">9. No Warranty</h2>
          <p class="uppercase font-medium text-white/90">
            The Software and Website are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We do not guarantee that GPU metrics will be perfectly accurate, that leak detection will catch every issue, or that the Software will be error-free or compatible with every hardware configuration. The Software provides monitoring data for informational purposes. Decisions you make based on its output are your responsibility.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 10. Limitation of Liability -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="uppercase font-medium text-white/90">
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, the Author shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including loss of profits, data, training runs, or goodwill, arising from your use of the Software or Website.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Our total liability for any claim is limited to the amount you paid us in the 12 months before the claim arose, or $0 if you are on the free tier.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Some jurisdictions do not allow these limitations. In those cases, our liability is limited to the maximum extent permitted by law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 11. Indemnification -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">11. Indemnification</h2>
          <p>
            You agree to indemnify and hold harmless the Author from claims, damages, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising from your use of the Software, violation of these Terms, or infringement of any third-party rights.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 12. Termination -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">12. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            Your license terminates automatically if you violate these Terms. You may terminate at any time by uninstalling the Software and ceasing all use. We may suspend or terminate access at any time, with or without cause.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            On termination, you must destroy all copies of the Software in your possession. Sections 4, 9, 10, 11, and 13 survive termination.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 13. Governing Law -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">13. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, USA, without regard to conflict of law principles.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Disputes shall first be subject to good-faith negotiation for 30 days. If unresolved, they shall be submitted to the state and federal courts in Suffolk County, Massachusetts.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 14. Changes -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">14. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms at any time. Updated Terms will be posted here with a revised effective date. Material changes will be communicated via email to users who have provided their address. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 15. General -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">15. General</h2>
          <p>
            If any provision of these Terms is unenforceable, the remaining provisions remain in effect. These Terms, together with the <a href="/privacy" class="text-cyan hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a> and any applicable subscription agreement, are the entire agreement between you and the Author regarding the Software and Website.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 16. Contact -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">16. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these Terms? Reach us at
            <a href="mailto:legal@gpulse.ai" class="text-cyan hover:underline">legal@gpulse.ai</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
